title: One Nation popularity rise to create ‘enormous problems’ for National Party
description: LNP MP Colin Boyce claims One Nation will create “enormous problems” for the National Party in regional electorates.  “The rise of One Nation will create enormous problems, particularly for the National Party,” Mr Boyce told Sky News Australia.  “Those big rural, regional electorates are quite happy to vote One Nation.”

title: Andrew should ‘absolutely pay the highest price’ following ‘horrific’ Epstein files images
description: ‘Triggered with Samara Gill’ host Samara Gill claims the images of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor uncovered in the latest documents to be released from the Jeffrey Epstein files are “absolutely horrific”.  There’s no suggestion of any wrongdoing, and Mr Mountbatten-Windsor has always denied allegations against him.  “This is someone who is in line to the British throne,” Ms Gill told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “Andrew should absolutely pay the highest price for what he did or what he didn’t do.”

title: ‘People are disgusted’: Bob Katter blasts Liberals and Nationals for ongoing dispute
description: Independent MP Bob Katter says people are “disgusted” by the ongoing dispute between the Nationals and the Liberals.  “You got nothing better to do than fight about who’s going to be the boss,” Mr Katter said.  “Do you realise how disgusted the people out there are with you?  “They are so desperate, they’re even going to vote for Pauline Hanson.”

title: ‘Like Tweedledee and Tweedledum’: Fergie brutally roasted over lavish praise of Epstein in emails
description: ‘Triggered with Samara Gill’ host Samara Gill has roasted Sarah Ferguson over comments she made in emails sent to Jeffrey Epstein which were revealed in the latest batch of documents from the files.  “I was just sifting through some of the emails last night, and some of the things that Fergie said to Epstein, I mean, they’re genuinely like Tweedledee and Tweedledum when you read what they said,” she told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “You know, ‘Oh please, please marry me, you’re my favourite’. It’s like they would do anything for a couple of thousand dollars.”

title: ‘We don’t need to be lectured to’: Celebrities ‘politicise’ Grammys with anti-ICE tirades
description: Adoni Media’s Leisa Goddard has reacted to some of the speeches from the Grammy winners who slammed ICE in their speeches.  “They should have no right to stand up there on that stage and politicise it,” she told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “They’re there because they are making a fortune as singers, so get up there, thank your mum, thank your dad, thank God, and then move on, we don’t need to be lectured to.”

title: ‘People are increasingly sick and tired’: Billie Eilish gives ‘absurd’ anti-ICE Grammys speech
description: Sky News host Freya Leach claims the Grammy Awards were full of the “typical political statements”.  “Obviously, one of the biggest moments in pop culture every year that people are increasingly sick and tired of,” Ms Leach said.  “It was full of the typical political statements. One of the most absurd ones came from Billie Eilish, who parroted a line that we’ve heard all too often here in Australia.”

title: ‘Gross incompetence or theft’: Trump blasts Fed Reserve over $4 billion renovation
description: US President Donald Trump has blasted the Federal Reserve over a $4 billion renovation.  “You’re doing a small renovation, and they’ve spent almost $4 billion doing a small renovation,” President Trump said.  “I don’t even see an end in sight.  “It’s either gross incompetence, or it’s theft of some kind or kickbacks.”

title: ‘Please marry me’: Shocking emails from Sarah Ferguson to Epstein revealed
description: ‘Triggered with Samara Gill’ host Samara Gill has commented on some of Sarah Ferguson’s emails revealed in the latest batch of documents released from the Jeffrey Epstein files.  “I was just sifting through some of the emails last night and some of the things that Fergie said to Epstein, I mean, they’re genuinely like Tweedledee and Tweedledum when you read what they said,” she told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “You know, ‘oh please, please marry me, you’re my favourite’. It’s like they would do anything for a couple of thousand dollars.”

title: ‘It’s not her fault’: Investigation into restored angel which looks like Giorgia Meloni
description: Sky News host Freya Leach discusses an investigation into claims about a restored angel in a church which has the likeness to Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni.  “Meloni just has a very angelic face,” she said.  “It’s not her fault she looks like an angel.”

title: Everything has ‘gone south’ for the Liberals since the federal election
description: Herald Sun Associate Editor James Campbell says credible polls have One Nation “basically neck and neck” with the Liberal Party.  Mr Campbell told Sky News Australia things have “gone south” for the Liberal Party since the federal election.  “All you need to know about the state of Australian politics is Albo was comfortable enough going back to the tennis and staying till late.”

title: Melania Trump’s documentary a box office hit as numbers have ‘gone through the roof’
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond discusses First Lady Melania Trump’s new documentary.  “The new Melania film was released over the weekend. We were talking about the fact they'd apparently sold no tickets last week,” Mr Bond said.  “But apparently the numbers show, compared to other docos, it’s gone through the roof.  “It’s one of those things the more you talk about it, the more people take an interest in it.”

title: Billie Eilish's 'stolen land' remark haunts singer as critics demand she give up her mansion
description: Singer Billie Eilish has faced backlash following her anti-Immigration & Customs Enforcement remarks at the 68th Annual Grammy Awards Show.  The 24-year-old singer declared that “no one is illegal on stolen land” while accepting the Song of the Year award for ‘Wildflower’.  Eilish’s remarks backfired as many have called for the singer to return her multi-million dollar mansion in Los Angeles to the original owners of the land.  “Billie Eilish calls America ‘stolen land,’” wrote one user.  “Ok, Billie. Your $14,000,000 mansion in LA is built where the Tongva tribes once lived. Any plans on returning it?”

title: Unhinged lefty podcast pushes insane conspiracy Trump's assassination attempt was staged
description: The co-hosts of the ‘I’ve Had It’ podcast have admitted their belief that the assassination attempt on President Trump’s life in Pennsylvania was fake.  Jennifer Welch went on the “permanent record” to say that she thinks the assassination was “totally” staged.  Co-host Angie Sullivan agreed with the conspiracy theory while nodding her head.  The podcast co-host then went on to claim that Trump is objectively a “Nazi fascist freakshow.”  Welch had previously laughed as she saw a left-wing activist celebrate Charlie Kirk’s death.

title: ‘A lot of angry people out there’: Aussies voting for ‘anybody’ other than major parties
description: Jacqui Lambie Network Senator Jacqui Lambie weighs in on the meteoric rise in One Nation polling numbers.   “One Nation is an angry party, and there is a lot of angry Australians out there at the moment who are really unsettled because of what is going on in world events,” Ms Lambie told Sky News Australia.   “The economy is not going as well for many people out there; they are struggling.  “There are a lot of disgruntled Australians … I’ll vote for anybody else but those parties.”

title: Leaders give chilling warning about the fall of Europe as Spain legalises 500,000 illegal immigrants
description: World leaders who have rejected the globalist agenda are speaking out and warning European nations of the dire consequences of their immigration policies.
